---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Terms — DeviceLab"
  description="How to use DeviceLab, what our rankings mean, and what we don't guarantee."
>
  <section class="dl-page-header">
    <div class="dl-eyebrow-hero">DEVICELAB / TERMS</div>
    <h1>Terms of use</h1>
    <p class="dl-blurb">
      What you can rely on, what you can't, and how our rankings
      actually work. Last updated: July 2026.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="dl-container" style="padding: 12px 16px 40px; max-width: 68ch;">
    <h2>The site</h2>
    <p>
      DeviceLab publishes independent, deterministic rankings of
      consumer computing devices. By using the site you agree to
      these terms. If you don't agree, please don't use it.
    </p>

    <h2>How rankings are produced</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Every device is scored 0–100 on six axes: performance, portability, display, battery, build, and value.</li>
      <li>The <strong>composite score is a weighted mean</strong> — you choose the weights via the mixer; each named "persona" is a preset weight vector.</li>
      <li><strong>Nothing about the ranking depends on affiliate offers, retail prices, sponsorships, or any other monetisation signal.</strong> The scoring engine lives in a code module with a hard boundary to the retail-links module. If a merchant tries to pay for a higher rank, the answer is no.</li>
      <li>Value is derived from performance-per-£ min-max normalised across the whole catalogue — not editorial.</li>
      <li>Ties break on value, then alphabetically.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>What we don't guarantee</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Prices and stock.</strong> The prices shown are
        indicative and reflect our seed data, not the merchant's live
        price. Always verify at the retailer before purchasing.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Specifications.</strong> We do our best to score devices
        accurately, but errors happen. Manufacturer sources take
        precedence over our figures.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Availability.</strong> Devices come and go from
        retailers' catalogues. A working button today may 404 tomorrow.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Ranking outcomes.</strong> The ranking is a heuristic to
        help you compare, not a personalised recommendation. Your
        needs may not map neatly to any preset.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Retail and affiliate links</h2>
    <p>
      Outbound links on device pages are affiliate links where a
      programme exists (Amazon Associates in the UK and US; Awin for
      participating manufacturers). We may earn a commission on
      qualifying purchases. This never affects rankings — the full
      disclosure lives on the <a href="/disclosure/">disclosure page</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>User-provided data</h2>
    <p>
      If you use the "Track price" form, you grant us permission to
      store your email and target price for the single purpose of
      emailing you once when the device hits that target. See the
      <a href="/privacy/">privacy policy</a> for detail.
    </p>

    <h2>Acceptable use</h2>
    <p>
      Don't scrape the site programmatically to rebuild the catalogue,
      don't attempt to circumvent the tri-state brand filter, and
      don't submit non-existent emails to the track-price endpoint —
      those are the only guardrails we have and they matter.
    </p>

    <h2>Liability</h2>
    <p>
      DeviceLab is provided "as is" without warranty of any kind. To
      the maximum extent permitted by law, we're not liable for any
      loss or damage arising from your use of the site or the
      accuracy (or lack of it) of any figure shown.
    </p>

    <h2>Governing law</h2>
    <p>
      These terms are governed by the laws of England and Wales. Any
      dispute is subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the English
      courts.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>
      If we change these terms materially, the date at the top updates.
    </p>
  </section>
</Base>
